    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a large knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until softened and crush the <strong>cardamom pod<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>, and <strong>crushed cardamom </strong>and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1612274711822-x200.jpg",
